wiki.text:
'Mona' may refer to: *{MONA} Drugs for Acute Coronary Syndrome
 M: morphine
 N: oxygen
 O: nitroglycerin
 P: aspirin. *Mona (deity) in Saxon mythology *[[Cercopithecus mona]], a long
    tailed African Monkey *Mona (elephant) (1947 - 2007) at Birmingham Zoo in
    the United States *Mona (name), a female given name and surname *Mona
    Charen, American columnist *Mona, ring name of Nora Greenwald
* MONA Missouri Nurses Association ;Ships and boats *Lifeboat Mona, a lifeboat
  based at Broughty Ferry in Scotland *, a United States Navy patrol boat in
  commission from 1918 to 1919 *, a Swedish coaster in service 1957-63

In 'arts and entertainment': *Mona (band), a Nashville-located alternative
rock band *''Mona'' (opera), a 1912 opera by Horatio Parker *"Mona", a song by
the Beach Boys from their album [[Love You (album)|Love You]] *"Mona", a song
by Bo Diddley *[[Mona – The Carnivorous Circus]], record by The Deviants
*[[Mona the Vampire]], an animated children's TV show or its protagonist *Mona
Simpson (''The Simpsons''), a character from the animated cartoon television
show *Mona Sax, a video game and film character in the [[Max Payne
(series)|Max Payne]] series *Mona (''WarioWare''), a character from the
Nintendo video game *A fictional animated Disney character in [[Christmas
Maximus]] (in Mickey's Twice Upon a Christmas) *[[Mona Lisa]], Leonardo da
Vinci's painting *[[Mona the Virgin Nymph]], also known as Mona, a 1970 film
that was one of the first pornographic films made for theatrical release in
the United States *Mona's Dream, a movie being worked on by Jack Lenz about
Mona Mahmudnizhad *Mona Mayfair, from the novels of Anne Rice *Museum of Neon
Art in Los Angeles, USA *Museum of Old and New Art the largest privately
funded museum in the southern hemisphere in Hobart, Tasmania, Australia. *MONA
FOMA, an arts festival held annually in Hobart, Tasmania curated by Brian
Ritchie, formerly of the Violent Femmes

In 'computing': *Monā, a Shift JIS art character in the Japanese BBS, 2channel
*Mona (operating system), an operating system from Japan *Mona, unseen character
of famous Gillette commercials in the 70s. Wife of unnamed onscreen character

'Places': *Mona, Jamaica, a residential neighbourhood of Kingston and home to
the University of the West Indies' main campus *Mona, Puerto Rico, an island in
the Mona Passage (from the Atlantic to the Caribbean Sea) *Mona, Utah, a town in
the United States *Mona, Anglesey, a village on the Welsh island Anglesey (in
the UK), also Latin name of that island *Two British isles, in poetic language
(from their Latin name): **Anglesey (Môn) **Isle of Man *Isle of Mona, a
fictionalized version of the Isle of Anglesey in Lloyd Alexander's "The
Chronicles of Prydain" series *Mona Vale (disambiguation), several geographic
locations in Australia.
